Yemen to Probe Deadly Clashes in Taiz Governorate, Saba Says

-- B y   V i v i a n   S a l a m a
-- 
2011-04-05T05:53:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/yemen-to-probe-deadly-clashes-in-taiz-governorate-saba-says.html
Yemen ’s government said it formed a
committee to investigate clashes in the governorate of Taiz this
week that killed at least 16 people and wounded hundreds, state-
run Saba news agency  reported today , citing Hamoud al-Soufi, the
governor of Taiz.  “We express our deep regret for the deviation of peaceful
protests,” the report quoted al-Soufi as saying. “We were
surprised by an attack on the governor’s building and the
Presidential Palace in Taiz.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vivian Salama in  Abu Dhabi  at 
 vsalama@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 